1. Arthur Hayes: The bull market goal may be "HYPE surpassing SOL";
2. Zhao Changpeng denied being the matchmaker for WLFI, saying that the WSJ report was a "fictional narrative";
3. Ethereum chain game Ember Sword announced its closure due to fund exhaustion, having set a record of $200 million in NFT sales;
4. Hyperliquid Labs submitted a letter of opinion to the CFTC, supporting the improvement of the DeFi regulatory framework;
5. Jump Crypto is suspected to be a market maker in the SOON market;
6. Sui urgently launched the whitelist function yesterday to prepare for the recovery of hacker funds;
7. Haedal: The haeVault function will be temporarily disabled to ensure user safety and protocol funds security.
